title: razgriz
body:
[i] "When history witnesses a great change, Razgriz reveals itself. First as a dark demon. As a demon, it uses its power to rain death upon the land, and then it dies. However, after a period of slumber, Razgriz returns. This time, as a great hero."[/i]

Mythical demon whose legend is told in [[ace_combat_5|Ace Combat 5: The Unsung War]]. 

Representing the duality of light and dark, the legend says that the Demon of Razgriz summoned a tempest that desecrated the land for seventy days, killing all those within, including the demon itself. However, after time passes, an old traveler comes to restore the land and bring new life to it, but when the traveler leaves, it announces that it too was Razgriz.

She later is adopted as the insignia of the aptly named Razgriz Squadron, otherwise called the "Ghosts of Razgriz" for their exceptional piloting skills and the fact that they [spoiler]fake their deaths after Hamilton, who was allied with the true antagonist, had deceived the Osean Air Defense Force into believing that Wardog Squadron were traitors.[/spoiler]

Use this tag when the Razgriz Squadron insignia is depicted or when an [[f-14_tomcat|F-14 Tomcat]] is deliberately using the black and red color scheme often associated with the Squadron.

title: help:array_syntax
body:
When searching by arrays, the following variations on search parameters can be used.

h5. Whitespace separated lists

These parameter variations use whitespace (spaces, tabs, linebreaks) as a separator for the array, regardless of whether the individual items are numbers or text. This is the default and has no qualifier.

h5. Array separated lists

These parameter variations use the URL array format to input the separate items. Is denoted with the qualifier "array".

[b]Example:[/b]

[code]
search[parameter1_include_any_array][]=foo&search[parameter1_include_any_array][]=bar
[/code]

The above sends the items as an array where it will end up as [code]["foo", "bar"][/code].

h5. Lowercase lists

These parameter variations apply a lowercase transformation to both the input and the record fields when making the comparisons. Is denoted with the qualifier "lower".

h5. Includes any

Will return all records that include any of the items from the array. Is denoted with the qualifier "include_any".

h5. Includes all

Will return all records that include all of the items from the array. Is denoted with the qualifier "include_all".

h5. Count

Searches using the count of items in the array. Uses the same parameter format as numbers (see [[Help:Number syntax]]).

h5. All parameter variations

For the following, [code]NAME[/code] is the name of the record field being searched for.

* [code]NAME_include_any[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_any_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_any_lower[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all_lower[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_any_lower_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all_lower_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_count[/code]

h4. See also

* [[Help:Boolean syntax]]
* [[Help:Number syntax]]
* [[Help:Text syntax]]
* [[Help:User syntax]]
* [[Help:API]]

title: rand_(gyee)
body:
A lumberman in seclusion.
He got displaced to avoid the White Cape.
There is detachment beside his handsome look.

As the eldest child, Rand was demanded by family to set a good example and be a 'model man'. However, he dared not let anyone in the conservative Crossport find out he is Gyee.

He kept the identity secret, concerned about causing the family 'shame' and 'dishonor', maybe even threats of death. He would hang out at an underground Gyee bar and vent with fellow kindred spirits, but then White Capes raided the enclave and hung all Gyee captives on the town square, dubbing them minions of the Shadow and evil 'Yellow Eyes', even announcing their intent to 'cleanse' Crossport.

That forced Rand to confess to his family and seek support. Although shocked by the revelation, they were more concerned about his safety and sneaked him out of Crossport, claiming publicly that Rand went to start a business far, far away.

Now, Rand works as a lumberjack near Eversun. He can finally be himself. Alone in the woods without friends or family, he welcomes every visiting Gyee with passion.

title: killing_bites
body:
A manga by [[Azuse Neko]].

People have been created that are human-animal hybrids, and powerful businesses bet on the outcome of their duels. College student Nomoto Yuuya's casual acquaintances ask him to drive them around to pick up girls one day, which he soon finds out means by force. The girl they kidnap is an animal-human hybrid named Hitomi, who slaughters all of them except Yuuya. Hitomi is a honey badger, which has been called the most fearless of all animals. Now Hitomi is assigned to stay with Yuuya, for his protection!


Killing Bites are underworld duels between human-animal hybrids.
One beast who knows no fear will fight in this animalistic world full of fear and insanity.

This ultimate battle of the beasts will shock you to your core!

title: keldeo
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #647 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Fighting Mythical Pokémon.

* [[Keldeo (Ordinary)]]: Keldeo is a quadruped, colt-like Pokémon with a cream-colored body. It has a short, rounded snout with large nostrils, and blue eyes. It has a large, feathery red mane, long, dark blue, ridged eyebrow-like protrusions, and a single cream-colored horn that curves slightly. The back of its head, as well as its neck, is covered with fluffy, light blue fur. Keldeo has blue hooves, which are capable of ejecting water. Its tail is light blue with white spots and resembles an elaborate feather in a cap.

* [[Keldeo (Resolute)]]: The dark blue protrusions become shorter and lighter in color, resembling ears. Its horn becomes dark blue, and grows larger and ridged. On the side of its head are three feathers colored aqua blue, green and orange.

Keldeo appears Resolute Form if it knows the move [i]Secret Sword[/i]; otherwise it appears in the Ordinary Form.

Alongside [[Cobalion]], [[Terrakion]] and [[Virizion]] it is member of the "Swords of Justice":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Swords_of_Justice.

It does not evolve from or into another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Keldeo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Kyurem]]
Next Pokémon: [[Meloetta]]

title: eclectus_parrot
body:
Latin: "[i]Eclectus roratus[/i]":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eclectus_parrot]

A species of parrot with extreme color-based sexual dimorphism.  Males have mostly bright emerald green plumage with red underwings while females are mostly bright red with a purple/blue belly and underparts.  

Until the early 20th century the sexes were considered different species.  

This parrot is native to the Solomon Islands, Sumba, New Guinea and nearby islands, northeastern Australia, and the Moluccas.  There are nine subspecies, some of which feature yellow plumage and other variations.

h4. See also
* "eBird - Eclectus Parrot":[https://ebird.org/species/eclpar]

title: koutetsujou_no_kabaneri
body:
[b]Koutetsujou no Kabaneri[/b] (甲鉄城のカバネリ, lit. [i]Kabaneri of the Iron Fortress[/i]) is an anime series by Wit Studio. The series is directed by Tetsurou Araki and written by Ichirou Oukouchi, with music by Hiroyuki Sawano and original character designs by Haruhiko Mikimoto. The series premiered on Fuji TV's Noitamina block on April 8, 2016.

A mysterious virus appears during the industrial revolution, infecting humans into Kabane and rapidly spreads. Kabane are aggressive, undead creatures that cannot be defeated unless the glowing heart, which is protected by a layer of iron, is pierced. Unfortunately, most melee weapons and the steam pressure guns used by the Bushi are not very effective against them. On the island country Hinomoto, people have built fortress-like stations to shelter themselves from these creatures. People access the stations and transport wares between them with the help of armored steam locomotives called Hayajiro. One day a Hayajiro hijacked by the Kabane crashes into Aragane station and they overrun the city. A young engineer called Ikoma uses the opportunity to test with success his anti-Kabane weapon, the TsuranukiI Zutsu, but is infected in the process, although he manages to resist the virus and become a Kabaneri, a human-Kabane hybrid. Assisted by Mumei, another Kabaneri who appears to help them, Ikoma and the other survivors of the station board the Hayajiro Kōtetsujō and depart to seek shelter elsewhere, fighting the hordes of Kabane along the way.

title: mao_jacket
body: (中山装/中山裝:Zhōngshān zhuāng) The modern chinese tunic suit as Zhongshan Suit by Sun Yat-sen, and later, the Mao Suit by Mao Zedong (Mao Tse-tung) Sun Yat-sen introduced the style shortly after the founding of the Republic of China as a form of national dress with distinct political overtones. He based the suit on the Japanese cadet uniform. The four pockets are said to represent the Four Virtues of propriety, justice, honesty, and shame; and the five buttons the branches of China's government, The 3 buttons at the end of sleeves represent the Three Principles of the People. The suits came to be worn widely by male citizens and government leaders as a symbol of civil servants, proletarian unity and an Eastern counterpart to the Western business suit.

title: cel
body:
Also called celluloids, they are plastic sheets used in traditional animation by hand-drawing and coloring images (or frames) on individual sheets, then shooting them in a sequence and then adding voices, music and SFX in post-production to create the effect of animation. This method of animation has been replaced with computer animation, so cel-animated shows are not widely seen anymore. They will contain punched holes to allow them to be stacked and/or aligned by means of a [[peg bar]]. The edges of a cell typically have a telltale unfinished look with rough brush strokes and discontinued lines, as the edges of the cels are meant to be cropped out of the final work.

For Danbooru, this tag refers to an individual frame of animation being scanned and uploaded.

h4. See also:
* [[production art]]
* [[animation paper]]
* [[peg bar]]

title: peg_bar
body:
A peg bar is a tool used in [[traditional media|traditional]] hand-drawn animation.  It consists of a metal bar with three pegs, and a hinged lid that snaps down on top.  They are used with [[animation paper]] or painted [[cel]]s which have been pre-punched with holes that fit the pegs.  A stack of sequential frames can be stacked onto a peg bar and the artist can flip back and forth between frames as they raw, or flip through all of the frames to get a rough idea of the animation in progress.

h4. See also:
* [[animation paper]]
* [[production art]]

h4. External links:
* "Wikipedia: Traditional Animation: Traditional ink-and-paint and camera":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traditional_animation#Traditional_ink-and-paint_and_camera]

title: animatic
body:
In animation and special effects work, the storyboarding stage may be followed by simplified mock-ups called "animatics" to give a better idea of how a scene will look and feel with motion and timing. At its simplest, an animatic is a sequence of still images (usually taken from a storyboard) displayed in sync with rough dialogue (i.e., scratch vocals) or rough soundtrack, essentially providing a simplified overview of how various visual and auditory elements will work in conjunction to one another.

These often feature simple [[lineart]] with lines in different colors (see: [[color trace]]) and are almost always low frame-rate and feature rough sketches as frames. They sometimes feature numbered cells indicating the order of the keyframes.

h4. See also:
* [[production art]]

title: princess_athena
body:
Princess Athena is the player character in the 1986 [[SNK]] platform game [[Athena (series)|]], also known as Athena's Wonder Land. She is supposed to be the Greek goddess Athena, and the whole game is themed on ancient mythology. The official name was originally just Athena, the title Princess was added over time and is maybe not official, but useful for a clearer distinction to her descendant [[Asamiya Athena]].

Princess Athena has long purple hair held by a golden barrette. She wears a red bikini and purple sandals, wields a sword and a round brass shield with spikes.

Princess Athena made a second appearance in SNK vs. Capcom: SVC Chaos as a secret boss. Her costume was only slightly modified. She got a red fingerless glove on her shield hand, a heart-shaped shield with a lion's head, some additional ribbons, her sandals got wings and her barrette got decorations that look as if it was a tied ribbon. This version should be labeled [[SVC Chaos]], the older one not.

In nude pictures, Princess Athena and Asamiya Athena can be distinguished by the barrette, which for the latter is usually red or white with a golden star, or (in [[the King of Fighters 2003|KoF 2003]]) gold with a red heart. However, sometimes artists use one of Asamiya Athena's barrettes when they obviously intend to draw Princess Athena.

title: shinka_musume
body:
Shinka Musume is a Chinese [[Virtual Youtuber|Virtual Uploader (虚拟UP主/VUP)]], originally created in 2013 to be the official 'mascot'/micro-blog image for China Central Television's Shinka Animation Channel. She was popular due to her original design sporting a distinct Beijing school uniform, but the channel went silent shortly after the reveal.

Later, in 2019, she was reintroduced as a virtual UP host on Bilibili. While she initially retained the red scarf she wore for her new redesign, emblematic of Chinese students, due to no longer being associated with CCTV and her original channel, the scarf was dropped.

title: dragon_quest_ii
body:
Full title: [i]Dragon Quest II: Akuryo no Kamigami[/i] (悪霊の神々, lit. "Pantheon of Evil Spirits")

The second game in the [i][[Dragon Quest]][/i] series, and the first in which the player controls a party of adventurers rather than just a single character.  Set one hundred years after the first game, the plot follows the descendants of the first [i]Dragon Quest[/i]'s hero as they struggle to free their world from the domination of the evil wizard Hargon.

Originally released for the [[Famicom]] in 1987, an English version was published for the NES in 1990 under the title [i]Dragon Warrior II[/i].  It has since been re-released several times, often combined with the original game, most notably for the [[Super Famicom]] and [[Game Boy Color]].

[i][[Dragon Quest Builders 2]][/i] follows after this game, which expands on the nature of the villains.

h4. See also

* DQ Wiki article: http://dragonquest.wikia.com/wiki/Dragon_Quest_II

title: el_gado
body:
An antagonist videogame character from [[Capcom]].

He first appeared in the [[Final Fight]] game from the 80s, and in many other fighting games since then. The first and only playable appearance of this character was in the game [i]Final Fight Revenge[/i].

[b]El Gado[/b] is part of the original [[Mad Gear]] gang that terrorized the streets of [[Metro City]]. He sports a beard and wears a greenish-yellow military outfit. He is of Arabic origin, and his fighting style is Souo-katsuken (Double Scorpion Tail technique). 

He works directly for [[Rolento]], along with [[Holly Wood]] (his palette-swap), [[Axl (Final Fight)|]] and Slash. They are the primary foot soldiers in Rolento's "army", all trained by Rolento himself. 

Both El Gado and Holly Wood are [[knife]]-wielding enemies who wear military style costumes, known for their agile movements which they forged by dancing. They have a special technique known as the "Jumping Knife Attack". These two also appeared in [[Street Fighter Zero (series)|]] 3 as part of Rolento's special techniques and win poses.

title: zweilous
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #634 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Dragon Pokémon.
Zweilous is a dark-blue, quadruped Pokémon with two heads and black fur covering its necks and back. Its front legs are muscular with two claws on each foot, but its rear legs are less defined and have two small, backward-pointing toes without claws. There are tufts of fur over its heads with rounded points at the top. It has two thin wings on its back, each ending in two points. The fur stops at the chest and opens up to fuchsia striped bands on the side of its legs. Though it appears to lack eyes, it is unknown if Zweilous is blind.

It evolves from [[Deino (Pokemon)|]] starting at level 50. It then evolves into Hydreigon starting at level 64. 
Japanese Name: [b]Dihead[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[deino_(pokemon)|Deino]]
Next Pokémon: [[Hydreigon]]

title: deino_(pokemon)
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #633 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Dragon Pokémon.
Deino is a small blue quadrupedal Pokémon with black fur covering its head and neck, concealing everything but its mouth from view. The fur around its neck also has six purple spots encircling it, which resemble bruises. The hair on the top of its head takes the shape of a single small horn. It also has a short tail that appears to be bitten off. As it is blind, it will bite at and eat anything that moves, and it has the vigor and energy to bite constantly and without stopping.

It evolves into [[Zweilous]] starting at level 50. Zweilous then evolves into [[Hydreigon]] starting at level 64.
Japanese Name: [b]Monozu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Durant]]
Next Pokémon: [[Zweilous]]

title: cubchoo
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #613 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Cubchoo is a bipedal, ursine Pokémon with a light blue head and neck. It has a slightly pointed head with large round ears, shiny, dark, oval eyes, and a darker blue muzzle. Cubchoo has a shiny dark nose, from which a considerable amount of light blue nasal mucus — the source of its attacks — droops. The lower part of its body is white. It has rounded forepaws, digit-less feet with black paw pads, and a small round tail. 

It evolves into [[Beartic]] starting at Level 37.
Cubchoo's nose is constantly running.
Japanese name: [b]Kumasyun[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Haxorus]]
Next Pokémon: [[Beartic]]

title: lampent
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #608 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fire/Ghost Pokémon.
Lampent has a clear, spherical head containing a bluish purple flame and oval, yellow eyes. On top of its head is a black covering, which resembles a lampshade, with a pointed spike on top. Underneath its head is a small, black body with a pointed spike at the bottom. Extending from its body are two long, wavy arms with no fingers. It floats through the air to move.

It evolves from [[Litwick]] and evolves into [[Chandelure]] with a [i]Dusk Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Lampler[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Litwick]]
Next Pokémon: [[Chandelure]]

title: klink
body:
[[Pokemon|Pokémon]] #599 in the National PokéDex, a Steel type Pokémon.
Klink resembles two interlocking gears with six teeth each. The teeth of the gears are a light gray, with a darker central region. Each gear has a white "X" in place of its left eye, while their right eyes have a black pupil and white sclera. They have round turquoise noses and small mouths. Klink can launch itself at opponents in the form of [i]Gear Grind[/i] and [i]Shift Gear[/i], its "signature moves":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Signature_move. 

It evolves into [[Klang]].
Japanese Name: [b]Giaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Ferrothorn]]
Next Pokémon: [[Klang]]

A further enhancement of the [[Crossbone Gundam X-1]] after the "Skull Heart" modification. The Full Cloth additional package, made with everything the SNRI had left once it became clear that maintaining the Crossbones was no longer possible, added multiple armor plates equipped with thrusters all over the unit, as well as the Skull Head Units containing I-Field generators for maximum defense. It was piloted by [[Tobia Arronax]], the former pilot of the [[Crossbone Gundam X-3]], whose wild and aggressive fighting style fit the mighty Full Cloth perfectly.

title: graze_ein
body:
[b]EB-AX2 Graze Ein[/b]
A large MS developed by Gjallarhorn. It was intended to work as a testbed for the Alaya-Vijnana System, which required that the human brain recognize the suit's body as its own. It was piloted by [spoiler]the remains of [[Ein Dalton]] after his body was damaged beyond repair.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]While the machine's performance allowed for Ein to take his revenge against Tekkadan, the real goal was to allow for the Alaya-Vijnana System to be used by anyone and without the recoil damage to the brain. This new version, dubbed the Type E, would be used by [[Gaelio Bauduin]] and [[McGillis Fareed]] in the wake of Ein's defeat.[/spoiler]

title: captive_bead_ring
body:
A captive bead ring (ball closure ring) is a type of body [[piercing]] jewelry. The captive bead or ball fits into a small opening in the circle of the ring. The bead is slightly larger than this opening and has small indentations or depressions that correspond to the ring's end-points so that it may fit snugly against them, thus completing the circuit of the ring. Often, a hole is drilled through the bead to allow easier fitting.

Captive bead rings can also have little accessories.

title: aka-san_to_kyuuketsuki
body:
A hentai visual novel.

Story summary from https://vndb.org/v12982 : 

"It was an odd time for Yuu to transfer to Niiyatomori Gakuen. Other than being able to fall fast asleep anywhere, he’s a pretty normal guy. Within half a month, he had made three friends. Shuugetsu is smart, handsome and a model student… if he could just keep his mouth shut. Shuugetsu’s osananajimi Kamui is an active girl who looks like a cool beauty… except she turns awfully delusional at the sight of anything cute. The long black-haired student council president Konoha is perfect in every way… until at important moments when extreme nervousness takes over.

The four of them are the only members of a dormitory within the school premises, which will be closed down for reasons relating to the declining birthrate. One day, a new transfer student and dorm mate arrived. The blond-haired Alexandra and her maid Ingot said they came to Japan to study meteorology, but she has a secret. Then one day, they found a child left behind in front of the dormitory."
